    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on LCL Consolidation in Pota Global Logistics (India) Pvt. Ltd., Chennai</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">G.Lokesh</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">LCL Consolidation<br />Global Logistics</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5750</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">This project focuses mainly about LCL Consolidation and how it is being done in a typical Freight Forwarding/NVOCC firm. We have also seen that there are many parties and their roles involved in LCL shipments. Logistics plays a vital role in all shipping activities and with respect to consolidation it plays a more significant role. In the primitive days as the logistics was not that much developed and its need was also not recognized, the LCL shipments was handled in such a way. Primarily LCL shipments were done in a un organized and un structured way when compared to the current scenario.
But now with the emergence of dedicated LCL consolidators who are professionally qualified in handling LCL shipments in a more structured and organized way by optimizing the cost, time, safety and customer satisfaction which are the key factors in the logistics of the shipping &amp; freight industry which also serve as backbone for any company’s success.
Future Growth:
To be a logistics winner in the coming years organizations need to use the downturn to reshape for growth, propelled by an unshakeable conviction that the mission is still important, that more prosperous times lie ahead, and that in some way the company infrastructure is helping to build a better kind of services to customers.
Logistics is inevitable in the future and essentially the management policy also has a significant role in the future of world. Generally the study is being featured with all aspects of management in Logistics and Freight areas. (Logistics include Transportation, Warehousing, Network Design, Cross docking, and Value Adding).
There is lot of scope in improving the infrastructure facilities in the logistics sector as the future of logistics sector is going to significantly contribute to the growth of country’s economy in the near future.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10548">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10548</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9711">MBA-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
